=Bio=

Enric Senabre Hidalgo (Spain) is currently a member of Dimmons Research Group (Internet Interdisciplinary Institute – UOC), and a visiting Fellow at the CECAN research centre (University of Surrey). He's a researcher working on co-design methodologies and Agile frameworks for research processes and the development of digital Commons. Previously, he was member of the Platoniq collective, co-founder and project manager of the platform [http://goteo.org/ Goteo.org] for civic crowdfunding. 

He is vice president of [http://www.cibersociedad.net/ Observatory for CyberSociety] and teaches about New Media and the history of Digital Culture at the [http://www.uoc.edu/ Open University of Catalonia], where he holds a Master's Degree in the Information and Knowledge Society. Also member of the Barcelona-based [[Escuela de Commons]]."

He's also co-founder of the [http://cometelobio.blogspot.com.es/ co-operative VerdNeda] in Barcelona,  consumer's group for the  purchase of NGM/organic food and ecological goods directly from local producers.

More info about Enric at his [http://www.estigmergia.net/wiki/About_me wiki]

